‘It made me laugh,’ Carrick said. ‘I can see Nev saying that, but it was quite nice in a way. Playing alongside Scholesy I learned so much. He’d take the ball anywhere, he’d put his foot on the ball and try to have influence on the game.

‘It is a lot about your personality, as a person, as a player, that is how I am really, quite quiet and understated, it suits me.’

