In the absence of Steven Gerrard and Frank Lampard, England’s midfield is crying out for an experienced head in the middle and Carrick, if he can stay injury free, is eyeing Euro 2016 as his tournament.

’That’s definitely what I’m striving towards,’ he added. ‘I’ d love to have another real crack at it. Trying to have a bigger influence in the team is the target.’

 

